[SN]TITLE[SN]
Glasgow pedestrian, 78, struck by car on Gallowgate dies

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 78-year-old man has died after being struck by a car in the east end of Glasgow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The collision took place at 20:45 on Friday on the Gallowgate at its junction with Abercromby Street. The car involved was a BMW 3 series.
The man was taken to hospital but died later. The road was closed for five hours to allow for investigation work.
Police have appealed for any witnesses to contact officers at Glasgow Divisional Road Policing Unit on 101.
